This paper proposes a solution for Multi-Source Neural Machine Translation (MSNMT) using a novel preprocessing technique. The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for translation, which falls under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed method, which is a common theme in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also mentions visualizing attention, which is a technique used in neural networks and falls under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of multilingual information, which is a common theme in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
